main event: A UFO observation was reported at McClellan AFB, California on 3/20/69, with the object being identified as likely Jupiter.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 1 hour and was noted as stationary,The object was described as having a magnitude similar to a very close planet,One observer at the base weather station and another at base operations confirmed the sighting,The object was observed at 240 degrees southwest of McClellan AFB,At least one observer has noted this object over the past year during clear nights.
witness description: One observer from the base weather station and one from base operations.
